  "response": "Yes, Kodak cameras are still around, but not in the same way they used to be. Here's a breakdown:\n\n*   **Kodak Alaris:** This company licenses the Kodak brand for a variety of products, including film, photographic paper, and some instant print cameras (like the Kodak Mini Shot and Kodak Printomatic). These are generally aimed at the consumer market. They are not the same company as the original Eastman Kodak Company.\n\n*   **Eastman Kodak Company:** This is the original company, which went through bankruptcy restructuring. Today, it focuses on commercial printing, packaging, and advanced materials and chemicals. They still produce some industrial and scientific imaging products.\n\nSo, while you can still buy cameras branded as \"Kodak\", they are typically manufactured and sold under license by Kodak Alaris. The Eastman Kodak Company is more involved in the industrial side of imaging now.",
